originalText.text: This "doctor" is a scam. I just received an email that she is closing her offices within "a few days/weeks"; if that doesn't show disregard for patients, try speaking with her on the phone. She's given patients less than 30 days notice to get an appointment "with limited appointments 1 day/week." She suggests that you find another PCP "ASAP" and only recommends Dr. Michelle Li in the area (without providing additional information on her either). You can't find any pictures of her online. She has never published any articles as a "doctor", her office is dirty, un-decorated, needs renovation, and is in a residential building (unsure whether this is legal). She cannot explain the medication she prescribes. She is not devoted to her profession and should be stripped of her license; I hope her imminent office closure relates to this.

originalText.text: Doctor charged me $60 for lab work for a preventative care visit and pocketed the money. Had to pay the lab again out of pocket after they told me they never received payment. Doctor then ignored my calls and texts and I had to report them to UHC’s fraud and abuse center. Beyond just the fraud, the staff was unprofessional and inexperienced and couldn’t operate an EGC at all. The physical office itself is just a repurposed apartment that is not clean or professional. Do not use this doctor no matter how urgent unless you don’t mind being scammed and being unable to trust their diagnosis.
